IT was a famous Saying of William Rufus, and is quoted to his Honour by


Hiſtorians; 
                              Whoſoever ſpares perjured Men, Robbers, Plunderers, and Traytors, deprives all good Men of their Peace and Quietneſs, and lays a Foundation of innumerable Miſchiefs to the Virtuous and Innocent.
